text: Paulette Guinchard-Kunstler (3 October 1949 – 4 March 2021) was a French politician. She was a member of the National Assembly representing Doubs's 2nd constituency from 1997 until 2001 and again from 2002 until 2007. She was a member of the Socialist Party. Guinchard-Kunstler was born in Reugney, France. Guinchard-Kunstler died of assisted suicide in Switzerland on 4 March 2021 at the age of 71. ==References== Category:1949 births Category:2021 deaths Category:Deaths by euthanasia Category:Politicians from Bourgogne-Franche- Comté Category:People from Doubs
